gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 130, Warriors 127
gameRecap.excerpt: Nikola Jokic hit a 39 foot three-pointer with time expiring to lift the Nuggets over the Warriors, 130-127. The Nuggets finished the final 6:34 on a 25-4 run to complete the comeback. Jokic recorded 34 points (13-16 FG), nine rebounds and 10 assists for the Nuggets, while Aaron Gordon added a season-high 30 points, along with nine rebounds in the victory. Stephen Curry tallied 30 points (5-12 3pt. FG) and six assists for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Nuggets have won back-to-back games as they improve to 25-11 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 16-18.
